    • Constructor Detail

      • Builder

        public Builder(@NonNull
               android.content.Context context,
               @NonNull
               OnTaskCompleteListener listener)
        Builder for the Contact Utilities class
        Parameters:
        context - Context
        listener - OnTaskCompleteListener The listener to pass data back on. Note! Data sent back will be a list of Contact Objects. See ContactUtilities.Contact. The data is sent back along the Listener with a tag to match the returned results: -Email: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_EMAIL -Phone: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_PHONE -Name: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_NAME -Address: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_ADDRESS -All Merged Contacts: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_ALL_MERGED_RESULTS -Progress Update: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_PROGRESS_UPDATE -No Results: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_NO_RESULTS -Missing READ_CONTACTS permission: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_MISSING_CONTACT_PERMISSION -Some Unknown Error: PGMacTipsConstants.TAG_CONTACT_QUERY_UNKNOWN_ERROR Bear in mind that the progressUpdate will only have data to send if the boolean flag for shouldUpdateProgress is set to true. shouldUpdateSearchProgress()

      • addAlphabetHeaders

        public ContactUtilities.Builder addAlphabetHeaders()
        Adds alphabetically ordered headers to the top to match the First name of the contact (raw display name). So P would be above Patrick in the contact list
        Returns:

      • useAllAlphabetHeaders

        public ContactUtilities.Builder useAllAlphabetHeaders()
        If this flag is passed, it will use all letters in the alphabet for the headers. IE, it will append A, B, C, D to the contact list regardless of matching names. If false, it will instead just put letter headers for actual contacts. For example, Bob and David will have 'B' and 'D' but no 'C' header.
        Returns:

      • moveFavoritesToTop

        public ContactUtilities.Builder moveFavoritesToTop()
        This flag will move favorites within the contact list to the top of the list. The favorites are selected via the contact app and not via this app.
        Returns:

      • onlyIncludeContactsWithPhotos

        public ContactUtilities.Builder onlyIncludeContactsWithPhotos()
        This flag will only return contacts if they have a photo with their contact object. If there is no photo, it will be omitted from the return results
        Returns:
        this
